    {
      "id": "cb1574b0-10fa-4958-8ce1-28870b6a5266",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The authors create goal clusters using latent variable mixture modelling and the results show that there is a misalignement between both sources of data. More specifically, self-repoorts before learning do not translate into learning relevant behaviour measurable by learning logs. More specifically, self-reports seem to be overly optimistic measures of student motivation and engagement.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "cb1574b0-10fa-4958-8ce1-28870b6a5266",
